    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-24T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="954"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d954">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/11894: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-24T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 24, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 24—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1080. Telegram No. 45 from Mr. Tittmann.<note n="26" xml:id="d954fn26">Harold H.
                        Tittmann, Jr., assistant to Myron C. Taylor, Personal Representative of the
                        President to Pope Pius XII.</note> It would be helpful if the Department
                    could let me have any evidence that may come to hand of increased religious
                    tolerance in Russia.</p>
                <p>Would it not be possible now for us to go further than we did in our recent
                    statement in which we repudiated for ourselves Communist principles and
                    doctrine? Could we not make a declaration in the sense that in lending our
                    support to Russia and in preparation for the peace we would hope that the Soviet
                    Government would abandon its attitude of religious and political intolerance and
                    adopt instead more humane and liberal policies? Some such pronouncement would
                    have reassuring effect on the Holy See and Catholic countries and it seems to me
                    on all decent people as well. [Tittmann.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
